#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
mixer — V2 Automatic DJ: Gapless Streamer with Intelligent Transitions
=======================================================================
This is the main entry-point for the Mixer project (V2).

Architecture
------------
The daemon is split into three concurrent layers:

1. **Audio Processor Thread** (`audio_processor_thread`)
   Runs in a background thread. Lazily loads one track at a time,
   asks the `DecisionEngine` to pick a transition, bakes the crossfade
   chunk, and writes it to `/dev/shm/` as a temporary WAV file. It then
   signals the main thread via a bounded `queue.Queue`.

2. **Decision Engine** (`DecisionEngine`)
   Analyses the *outgoing* track's last 5 s and the *incoming* track's
   first 5 s. Extracts four features — total RMS, bass RMS (< 250 Hz),
   treble RMS (> 2 kHz), and energy variance — and applies a rule-based
   priority waterfall to select one of seven transition styles.

3. **Main Loop** (`main`)
   Runs the mpv subprocess with IPC enabled. Polls mpv's playlist via
   the Unix domain socket to determine how many tracks are queued ahead
   of the currently playing one, then feeds the next processed chunk
   from the queue when the buffer runs low. Also handles `/dev/shm`
   garbage-collection of already-played chunks.

Transition Styles
-----------------
fade         Classic equal-power (sinusoidal) crossfade.
blend        Extended 10 s overlap with equal-power curves — ideal for
             EDM / Techno where tracks share a similar BPM.
rise         Progressive 0→+4 dB swell on the incoming track to
             emphasise an energy surge or "drop".
cut_in       Hard cut with a 15 ms anti-pop micro-fade guard.
bass_swap    Progressive high-pass sweep (80 → 800 Hz, exponential) on
             the outgoing track + 120 Hz HP kill on the incoming track
             to prevent muddy low-end collisions.
filter_wash  Progressive high-pass sweep (80 → 2000 Hz) with a
             resonance bump tracking the cutoff, making the outgoing
             track sound increasingly thin and distant.
melt         Multi-echo atmospheric dissolve (three tap delays at
             200 / 400 / 700 ms) with soft low-pass smoothing at 3 kHz.
tape_stop    Tape crossfade — progressive tape/turntable slowdown on the
             outgoing track overlaid with an equal-power fade-in of the
             incoming track, so the new track emerges as the old one
             winds down.

Dependencies
------------
    pip install pydub
    apt install mpv ffmpeg    # (or brew install mpv ffmpeg on macOS)

Usage
-----
    cd /path/to/music/folder
    mixer

Supported formats: mp3, m4a, wav, opus, flac, ogg, aac, webm.
Processed chunks are staged in /dev/shm/ (RAM filesystem) and
automatically cleaned up after playback.
"""

